WEBVTT

1
00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:36.400
GAME OF THRONES

2
00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:40.720
Episode 9

3
00:02:02.200 --> 00:02:04.480
You've seen better days.
my lord.

4
00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:06.920
Another visit?

5
00:02:08.680 --> 00:02:10.520
It seems
you're my last friend.

6
00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:13.200
No. no.
Many still love you.

7
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.320
Sansa came to court this morning
to plead for your life.

8
00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:23.440
On her knees? Begging for me?
And did you laugh with the others?

9
00:02:24.560 --> 00:02:27.760
You do me wrong. my lord. Your
blood is the last thing I want.

10
00:02:28.040 --> 00:02:31.320
You don't know what you want.
I've given up trying to guess.

11
00:02:34.920 --> 00:02:39.560
When I was still a boy. before they
cut off my balls off with a hot knife.

12
00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:43.640
I traveled with a group of actors
through the Free Cities.

13
00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:48.120
They taught me that each man
has a role to play.

14
00:02:49.360 --> 00:02:52.680
The same is true at court.
I am the master of whisperers.

15
00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:56.600
My role is to be sly and
obsequious and without scruples.

16
00:02:58.280 --> 00:03:00.160
I'm a good actor. my lord.

17
00:03:01.520 --> 00:03:03.240
Can you free me
from this pit?

18
00:03:03.520 --> 00:03:05.080
I could.

19
00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:07.320
But will I? No.

20
00:03:09.200 --> 00:03:10.920
As I said. I'm no hero.

21
00:03:11.240 --> 00:03:13.920
What do you want? Tell me.
no riddles. no stories.

22
00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:15.960
tell me what you want.

23
00:03:17.520 --> 00:03:19.280
Peace.

24
00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:22.960
Did you know that your son marches
south with an army of northmen?

25
00:03:23.680 --> 00:03:26.440
Loyal lad! Fighting
for his father's freedom...

26
00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:30.440
Robb? He's only a boy...

27
00:03:31.480 --> 00:03:33.560
Boys have been
conquerors before.

28
00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:37.080
But the man giving Cersei
sleepless nights is the king's...

29
00:03:37.840 --> 00:03:40.080
the late king's brother.

30
00:03:40.320 --> 00:03:42.720
Lord Stannis has the best claim
to the throne.

31
00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:46.160
He's a proven battle commander
and he's utterly without mercy.

32
00:03:46.400 --> 00:03:48.600
Stannis Baratheon
is Robert's true heir.

33
00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:50.800
The throne is his by rights.

34
00:03:52.080 --> 00:03:54.600
Sansa begged so sweetly
for your life.

35
00:03:54.840 --> 00:03:56.960
it would be a shame
to throw it away.

36
00:03:58.320 --> 00:04:02.120
Cersei's no fool. She knows
a tame wolf is more use to her

37
00:04:02.240 --> 00:04:04.000
than a dead one.

38
00:04:04.120 --> 00:04:06.560
You want me to serve the woman
who murdered my king.

39
00:04:06.680 --> 00:04:08.760
butchered my men
and crippled my son?

40
00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:10.920
I want you
to serve the realm.

41
00:04:11.520 --> 00:04:14.200
Tell the queen you will
confess your vile treason.

42
00:04:14.280 --> 00:04:18.080
tell your son to lay down his sword.
and proclaim Joffrey as the true heir.

43
00:04:20.440 --> 00:04:22.880
Cersei knows
you're a man of honor.

44
00:04:24.440 --> 00:04:27.200
If you give her the peace she needs
and promise to carry

45
00:04:27.280 --> 00:04:29.920
her secret to your grave.
I believe she'll allow you

46
00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.640
to take the black and live out
your days on the Wall.

47
00:04:32.720 --> 00:04:35.040
with your brother
and your bastard son.

48
00:04:35.840 --> 00:04:38.280
You think my life is some
precious thing to me.

49
00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:42.560
that I would trade my honor
for a few more years of...

50
00:04:42.960 --> 00:04:44.800
of what?

51
00:04:49.240 --> 00:04:51.120
You grew up with actors.

52
00:04:52.600 --> 00:04:55.120
You learned their craft
and you learned it well.

53
00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:58.600
But I grew up with soldiers.

54
00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:03.240
I learned how to die
a long time ago.

55
00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:09.760
A pity. Such a pity.

56
00:05:17.080 --> 00:05:19.120
What of your daughter's life.
my lord?

57
00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:22.080
Is that a precious thing
to you?

58
00:06:01.880 --> 00:06:04.520
It's a birthday message
to his grand-niece Walda.

59
00:06:04.680 --> 00:06:06.680
Or so Walder Frey
would have you think.

60
00:06:06.760 --> 00:06:09.280
Keep shooting them down.
We can't risk Lord Walder

61
00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:11.880
sending word of your movements
to the Lannisters.

62
00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:15.040
He's grandfather's bannerman.
We can't expect his support?

63
00:06:15.120 --> 00:06:18.200
Expect nothing of Walder Frey.
and you will never be surprised.

64
00:06:18.280 --> 00:06:20.160
Look.

65
00:06:21.320 --> 00:06:24.520
Father rots in a dungeon.
How long before they take his head?

66
00:06:25.960 --> 00:06:28.400
We need to cross the Trident
and we need to do it now.

67
00:06:28.520 --> 00:06:30.960
March up to his gates
and tell him you're crossing.

68
00:06:31.040 --> 00:06:33.880
We've got five times his numbers.
You can take the Twins.

69
00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.920
Not in time. Tywin Lannister
marches north as we speak.

70
00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:39.400
The Freys have held the crossing
for 600 years.

71
00:06:39.480 --> 00:06:41.920
and they have never failed
to exact their toll.

72
00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:44.600
Have my horse saddled
and ready.

73
00:06:44.920 --> 00:06:48.360
Enter the Twins alone and he'll sell
you to the Lannisters as he likes.

74
00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:50.920
Or throw you in a dungeon.
Or slit your throat.

75
00:06:53.400 --> 00:06:56.360
My father would do whatever it took
to secure our crossing.

76
00:06:56.480 --> 00:06:58.280
Whatever it took.

77
00:06:58.760 --> 00:07:00.800
As leader of this army.
I can't have other men

78
00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:02.760
doing my bargaining for me.

79
00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:06.400
I agree. I'll go.

80
00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:09.160
I've known Lord Walder
since I was a girl.

81
00:07:09.840 --> 00:07:11.680
He would never harm me.

82
00:07:12.160 --> 00:07:14.240
Unless there was
a profit in it.

83
00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:21.240
What do you want?

84
00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:24.600
It is a great pleasure to see you
after so many years my lord.

85
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:29.360
Spare me. Your boy's too proud
to come before me himself.

86
00:07:30.600 --> 00:07:32.520
What am supposed
to do with you?

87
00:07:32.680 --> 00:07:34.520
Father...
you forget yourself.

88
00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:36.840
- Lady Stark...
- Who asked you?

89
00:07:37.240 --> 00:07:39.920
You're not Lord Frey yet.
not until I die.

90
00:07:40.120 --> 00:07:42.480
- Do I look dead to you?
- Father. please...

91
00:07:42.560 --> 00:07:45.200
I need lessons in courtesy
from you. bastard?

92
00:07:46.040 --> 00:07:47.920
Your mother would still be
a milkmaid

93
00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:50.280
if I hadn't squirted you
into her belly.

94
00:07:54.080 --> 00:07:56.400
Alright. you come forward.

95
00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:11.000
There. Now that I have done
the courtesy. perhaps my sons

96
00:08:11.080 --> 00:08:13.560
will do me the honor
of shutting their mouths.

97
00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:22.320
- Is there somewhere we can talk?
- We're talking now.

98
00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:28.760
Fine. Out!

99
00:08:29.680 --> 00:08:31.640
All of you!

100
00:08:40.840 --> 00:08:42.560
You too!

101
00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:52.120
You see that?
Fifteen. she is.

102
00:08:53.480 --> 00:08:55.320
A little flower.

103
00:08:56.640 --> 00:08:58.760
And her honey's all mine.

104
00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:03.720
I'm sure she will give you
many sons.

105
00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:07.600
Your father didn't come
to the wedding.

106
00:09:07.760 --> 00:09:09.520
He is quite ill. my lord.

107
00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:13.640
Didn't come to the last one either.
or the one before that.

108
00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:18.480
Your family
has always pissed on me.

109
00:09:18.880 --> 00:09:21.000
Don't deny it!
You know it's true.

110
00:09:21.560 --> 00:09:25.000
The fine Lord Tully would never
marry any of his children to mine.

111
00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:28.800
- I'm sure there were reasons...
- I didn't need reasons!

112
00:09:29.240 --> 00:09:31.440
I needed to get rid
of sons and daughters.

113
00:09:31.520 --> 00:09:33.400
You see how they pile up.

114
00:09:36.920 --> 00:09:38.520
Why are you here?

115
00:09:41.080 --> 00:09:45.840
To ask you to open your gates.
so my son and his bannermen

116
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.360
can cross the Trident
and be on their way.

117
00:09:48.440 --> 00:09:50.080
Why should I let him?

118
00:09:50.160 --> 00:09:52.920
If you could climb your own
battlements. you would see

119
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:55.640
that he has twenty thousand men
outside your walls.

120
00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:59.200
They'll be twenty thousand corpses
when Tywin Lannister gets here.

121
00:09:59.280 --> 00:10:01.160
Don't try to frighten me.
Lady Stark.

122
00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:03.520
Your husband's in a cell
beneath the Red Keep.

123
00:10:03.640 --> 00:10:06.160
and your son's got no fur
to keep his balls warm.

124
00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:08.120
You swore an oath
to my father.

125
00:10:08.200 --> 00:10:13.320
Oh yes. I said some words...
but I swore oaths to the crown too.

126
00:10:13.440 --> 00:10:16.520
if I remember right.
Joffrey's king now.

127
00:10:16.640 --> 00:10:20.400
which makes your boy and his
corpses-to-be nothing but rebels.

128
00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:22.200
it seems to me.

129
00:10:23.240 --> 00:10:25.280
If I had the sense
the gods gave a fish.

130
00:10:25.360 --> 00:10:27.480
I'd hand you both
over to the Lannisters.

131
00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:29.320
Why don't you?

132
00:10:29.400 --> 00:10:31.800
Stark. Tully. Lannister.
Baratheon...

133
00:10:33.440 --> 00:10:36.960
give me one good reason why I should
waste a thought on any of you?

134
00:10:42.640 --> 00:10:45.240
When does Aemon think you'll be
able to use that hand?

135
00:10:45.640 --> 00:10:47.200
Soon. he said.

136
00:10:47.320 --> 00:10:49.960
Good. You'll be ready
for this. then.

137
00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:55.320
A wolf seemed more appropriate
for you than a bear.

138
00:10:57.360 --> 00:11:00.320
So I had a new pommel made.
called Longclaw.

139
00:11:01.160 --> 00:11:04.800
Works as well for wolves
as for bears. I think.

140
00:11:14.840 --> 00:11:16.760
This is Valyrian steel.

141
00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:20.800
It was my father's sword.
and his father's before him.

142
00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:24.440
The Mormonts have carried it
for five centuries.

143
00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:27.000
It was meant
for my son. Jorah.

144
00:11:27.840 --> 00:11:31.360
He brought dishonor upon our house.
but at least he had the grace

145
00:11:31.480 --> 00:11:34.080
to leave the sword
before he fled from Westeros.

146
00:11:35.840 --> 00:11:37.800
My lord... you honor me.
but I can't.

147
00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:41.200
You can and you will.
I wouldn't be sitting here

148
00:11:41.320 --> 00:11:43.640
if it weren't for you
and your beast.

149
00:11:45.080 --> 00:11:47.160
A bloody dead man
tried to kill me.

150
00:11:49.480 --> 00:11:52.160
You'll take it.
and I'll hear no more of it.

151
00:11:53.520 --> 00:11:55.600
- Is that understood?
- Yes. my lord.

152
00:11:57.160 --> 00:11:59.920
And don't think this means
I approve of that nonsense

153
00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:02.120
between you
and Alliser Thorne.

154
00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:05.360
That's a man's sword
you have there.

155
00:12:05.440 --> 00:12:07.400
and it'll take a man
to wield it.

156
00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:10.000
I'll apologize
to Ser Alliser tonight.

157
00:12:10.080 --> 00:12:12.880
No you won't. I sent him
to King's Landing yesterday.

158
00:12:13.120 --> 00:12:16.360
The hand your wolf tore off
that thing's wrist...

159
00:12:16.600 --> 00:12:20.760
I've commanded Thorne to lay it
at the feet of this boy king.

160
00:12:22.400 --> 00:12:24.600
Should get
young Joffrey's attention.

161
00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:29.560
And it puts a thousand leagues
between you and Thorne.

162
00:12:31.120 --> 00:12:33.280
Now go put that sword
somewhere safe.

163
00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:35.880
and then bring me my supper.

164
00:12:36.400 --> 00:12:38.040
Yes. my lord.

165
00:12:49.160 --> 00:12:50.960
Well done.

166
00:12:52.680 --> 00:12:54.640
You earned that. Snow.

167
00:12:57.960 --> 00:12:59.640
Well done.

168
00:13:04.400 --> 00:13:06.440
- Go on. let's have a look.
- At what?

169
00:13:06.560 --> 00:13:08.440
The sword!
Show us the sword!

170
00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:10.480
Sword! Sword!

171
00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:26.160
I wanna have a look at it
in the light.

172
00:13:31.560 --> 00:13:33.280
What is it?

173
00:13:35.840 --> 00:13:38.400
- I can't.
- Can't what?

174
00:13:41.960 --> 00:13:43.960
I'm really not supposed
to say...

175
00:13:44.760 --> 00:13:46.920
And yet.
you really want to say...

176
00:13:47.600 --> 00:13:49.520
You want to say that...

177
00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:56.400
There was a raven. I read
the message to Maester Aemon.

178
00:13:59.280 --> 00:14:03.480
- It's your brother. Robb.
- What!? What about him?

179
00:14:05.840 --> 00:14:08.120
He's heading south. to war.

180
00:14:10.680 --> 00:14:12.920
All his bannermen
have rallied to his side.

181
00:14:13.040 --> 00:14:15.240
They'll keep him safe.

182
00:14:16.320 --> 00:14:18.200
I should be there.

183
00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:22.200
I should be with him.

184
00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:41.800
Well?

185
00:14:42.080 --> 00:14:43.920
What did he say?

186
00:14:44.560 --> 00:14:46.840
Lord Walder has granted
your crossing.

187
00:14:48.960 --> 00:14:52.520
His men are yours as well.
less the 400 he'll keep here

188
00:14:52.640 --> 00:14:55.520
to hold the crossing
against any who would pursue you.

189
00:14:55.640 --> 00:14:57.360
And what does he want
in return?

190
00:14:57.480 --> 00:15:00.720
You'll be taking on his son
Olyvar as your personal squire.

191
00:15:01.120 --> 00:15:03.120
He expects a knighthood.
in good time.

192
00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:04.960
Fine. fine.

193
00:15:05.960 --> 00:15:07.800
And?

194
00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:13.880
And Arya will marry his son Waldron
when they both come of age.

195
00:15:14.400 --> 00:15:16.520
She won't be happy
about that.

196
00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:22.080
And?

197
00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:26.360
And. when the fighting is done.

198
00:15:29.200 --> 00:15:31.360
you will marry
one of his daughters.

199
00:15:32.440 --> 00:15:34.400
Whichever you prefer.

200
00:15:34.720 --> 00:15:37.280
He has a number
he thinks will be suitable.

201
00:15:37.880 --> 00:15:39.840
I see.

202
00:15:41.480 --> 00:15:43.600
Did you get
a look at his daughters?

203
00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:45.880
I did.

204
00:15:46.360 --> 00:15:49.640
- And?
- One was...

205
00:15:56.200 --> 00:15:59.120
- Do you consent?
- Can I refuse?

206
00:15:59.640 --> 00:16:01.760
Not if you want to cross.

207
00:16:05.040 --> 00:16:06.920
Then I consent.

208
00:16:50.200 --> 00:16:52.200
Sam said you wanted
to see me?

209
00:16:52.560 --> 00:16:54.240
I did indeed.

210
00:16:54.760 --> 00:16:57.160
Perhaps you will be
kind enough to assist me.

211
00:17:00.760 --> 00:17:04.720
Did you ever wonder why the men
of the Night's Watch

212
00:17:05.960 --> 00:17:08.240
take no wives
and father no children?

213
00:17:09.080 --> 00:17:10.880
No.

214
00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:14.960
So they will not love.
Love is the death of duty.

215
00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:19.320
If the day should
ever come when your lord father

216
00:17:19.400 --> 00:17:22.280
was forced to choose between honor
on the one hand

217
00:17:23.080 --> 00:17:25.960
and those he loves on the other.
what would he do?

218
00:17:28.760 --> 00:17:31.240
He would do whatever was right.
No matter what.

219
00:17:32.800 --> 00:17:35.320
Then Lord Stark is one man
in ten thousand.

220
00:17:36.600 --> 00:17:38.400
Most of us
are not so strong.

221
00:17:39.320 --> 00:17:42.880
What is honor compared
to a woman's love?

222
00:17:44.400 --> 00:17:49.000
What is duty against the feel
of a newborn son in your arms...

223
00:17:50.480 --> 00:17:52.520
or a brother's smile?

224
00:17:56.200 --> 00:17:57.960
Sam told you.

225
00:17:58.120 --> 00:18:01.040
We are all human.
We all do our duty.

226
00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:04.240
when there is no cost to it.
Honor comes easy. then.

227
00:18:05.360 --> 00:18:10.080
Yet sooner or later
in every man's life.

228
00:18:11.200 --> 00:18:13.720
there comes a day
when it is not easy.

229
00:18:14.800 --> 00:18:16.920
A day when he must choose.

230
00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:21.760
And this is my day?
Is that what you're saying?

231
00:18:23.040 --> 00:18:25.560
It hurts. boy. Oh yes.

232
00:18:26.320 --> 00:18:30.760
- I know.
- You don't know. No one knows.

233
00:18:34.560 --> 00:18:37.160
I may be a bastard.
but he is my father.

234
00:18:37.360 --> 00:18:39.680
And Robb is my brother.

235
00:18:42.880 --> 00:18:45.760
The gods were cruel when they saw
fit to test my vows.

236
00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:49.280
They waited until I was old.

237
00:18:50.520 --> 00:18:53.840
What could I do when the ravens
brought the news from the south?

238
00:18:54.640 --> 00:18:57.200
The ruin of my house.
The death of my family.

239
00:18:57.560 --> 00:19:00.960
I was helpless.
blind and frail...

240
00:19:05.160 --> 00:19:08.240
And yet. when I heard
they'd killed my brother's son.

241
00:19:09.200 --> 00:19:12.160
and his poor son...
and the children...

242
00:19:12.880 --> 00:19:15.320
even the little children...

243
00:19:17.120 --> 00:19:19.080
Who are you?

244
00:19:20.880 --> 00:19:25.160
My father was Maekar.
the First of his Name.

245
00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:32.320
My brother Aegon reigned after him.
when I had refused the throne.

246
00:19:33.320 --> 00:19:35.880
And he was followed
by his son. Aerys.

247
00:19:36.840 --> 00:19:39.120
Whom they called
the Mad King.

248
00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:42.120
You're Aemon Targaryen?

249
00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:48.080
I am a Maester of the Citadel.
bound in service to Castle Black

250
00:19:48.480 --> 00:19:50.600
and the Night's Watch.

251
00:19:53.040 --> 00:19:58.760
I will not tell you to stay or go.
You must make that choice yourself.

252
00:20:00.800 --> 00:20:03.560
live with it for
the rest of your days.

253
00:20:06.920 --> 00:20:08.800
As I have.

254
00:20:26.760 --> 00:20:28.760
My lord.

255
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:31.040
My sun and stars.

256
00:20:33.160 --> 00:20:35.040
Drogo.

257
00:20:46.040 --> 00:20:47.920
My horse...

258
00:20:48.080 --> 00:20:50.080
Blood of my blood.

259
00:20:50.200 --> 00:20:52.600
No. I must ride...

260
00:20:53.600 --> 00:20:55.840
He fell from his horse.

261
00:20:56.440 --> 00:20:59.920
A Khal who cannot ride
is no Khal.

262
00:21:00.160 --> 00:21:02.680
He's tired. that's all.
He needs to rest.

263
00:21:03.600 --> 00:21:07.520
We've ridden far enough today.
We'll camp here.

264
00:21:07.760 --> 00:21:09.880
This is no place to camp.

265
00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:13.040
A woman does not give us orders.
Not even a khaleesi.

266
00:21:13.160 --> 00:21:16.080
We camp here. Tell them
Khal Drogo commanded it.

267
00:21:16.200 --> 00:21:18.920
You do not command me.
Khaleesi.

268
00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:22.600
Find Mirri Maz Duur.
Bring her to Jm.

269
00:21:22.680 --> 00:21:25.200
The witch?
I'll bring you her head.

270
00:21:25.320 --> 00:21:28.040
Bring her to me. unharmed.

271
00:21:28.680 --> 00:21:31.400
or Khal Drogo will hear
why you defied me.

272
00:21:58.480 --> 00:22:01.880
Our scouts tell us the Stark host
has moved south from the Twins.

273
00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:04.360
with Lord Frey's levies in tow.

274
00:22:04.520 --> 00:22:06.640
They are
a day's march north.

275
00:22:07.120 --> 00:22:09.920
The boy may lack experience
and sense. but he does have

276
00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:13.600
a certain mindless.
provincial courage...

277
00:22:18.680 --> 00:22:20.960
Do continue.
Didn't mean to interrupt.

278
00:22:21.040 --> 00:22:23.200
I hope your savages will be
of use.

279
00:22:23.320 --> 00:22:25.480
Otherwise we've wasted
good steel on them.

280
00:22:25.560 --> 00:22:28.520
The great hairy one insisted
he must have two battle axes.

281
00:22:28.600 --> 00:22:31.000
Heavy black steel.
double-sided.

282
00:22:31.120 --> 00:22:33.040
Shagga likes axes.

283
00:22:33.160 --> 00:22:35.720
When the battle commences.
you and your wildlings

284
00:22:35.800 --> 00:22:37.560
will be in the vanguard.

285
00:22:37.640 --> 00:22:39.280
The vanguard?

286
00:22:39.360 --> 00:22:41.480
Me and the tribesmen.

287
00:22:41.840 --> 00:22:44.160
They do seem
rather ferocious.

288
00:22:47.440 --> 00:22:51.800
Last night. a Moon Brother stabbed
a Stone Crow over a sausage.

289
00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:55.440
Three Stone Crows seized the
Moon Brother and opened his throat.

290
00:22:55.520 --> 00:22:58.640
Bronn kept Shagga from
chopping off the dead man's cock.

291
00:22:58.720 --> 00:23:02.400
which was fortunate. but even so.
Ulf is demanding blood money.

292
00:23:02.480 --> 00:23:05.520
which Gunthor and Shagga
refuse to pay.

293
00:23:05.640 --> 00:23:08.840
When soldiers lack discipline.
fault lies with their commander.

294
00:23:08.920 --> 00:23:11.520
Surely there are ways to have me
killed that would be

295
00:23:11.600 --> 00:23:13.360
less detrimental
to the war effort.

296
00:23:13.440 --> 00:23:15.960
There will be no more
discussion on the matter.

297
00:23:19.960 --> 00:23:23.000
It seems I'm not hungry after all.
You'll excuse me. my lords.

298
00:23:36.840 --> 00:23:39.280
Where did you find one
this pretty at this hour?

299
00:23:39.480 --> 00:23:42.440
- I took her.
- Took her from whom?

300
00:23:43.520 --> 00:23:46.080
From Ser... what's his name?

301
00:23:46.960 --> 00:23:49.640
I dunno. some ginger cunt
three tents down.

302
00:23:50.240 --> 00:23:52.520
And he didn't have
anything to say about it?

303
00:23:52.680 --> 00:23:54.880
He said something.

304
00:23:57.600 --> 00:24:01.080
Well. the odds of me living
long enough for him to retaliate

305
00:24:01.280 --> 00:24:04.680
just dropped drastically.
We'll be at the vanguard tomorrow.

306
00:24:13.280 --> 00:24:15.360
I think I'll go
find myself one.

307
00:24:19.080 --> 00:24:21.760
- Who are you?
- Who would you like me to be?

308
00:24:23.000 --> 00:24:24.840
What did your mother call you?

309
00:24:25.120 --> 00:24:27.600
Shae. What did
your mother call you?

310
00:24:28.240 --> 00:24:30.240
My mother died
giving birth to me.

311
00:24:30.640 --> 00:24:33.480
Is that why I'm here? So we can
talk about our mothers?

312
00:24:34.560 --> 00:24:36.840
- What kind of accent is that?
- Foreign.

313
00:24:40.480 --> 00:24:43.480
- What do you want from me?
- What do I want from you...

314
00:24:46.080 --> 00:24:50.240
I want you to share my tent.
pour my wine. laugh at my jokes.

315
00:24:50.680 --> 00:24:53.520
and rub my legs when they're sore
after a day's ride.

316
00:24:53.880 --> 00:24:57.320
I want you to take no other man to bed
for as long as we're together.

317
00:24:57.440 --> 00:25:00.800
And I want you to fuck me like
it's my last night in this world.

318
00:25:01.760 --> 00:25:03.800
Which it may well be.

319
00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:05.680
And what do I get?

320
00:25:05.800 --> 00:25:07.520
One: safety.

321
00:25:08.240 --> 00:25:10.760
No one will hurt you
for as long as you're mine.

322
00:25:11.880 --> 00:25:16.320
Two: the pleasure of my company.
Which. I've heard. is spectacular.

323
00:25:17.080 --> 00:25:19.360
Who told you this?
Women you paid?

324
00:25:19.520 --> 00:25:24.320
And three: more gold than you could
spend if you lived a thousand years.

325
00:25:26.600 --> 00:25:28.640
Do you accept my proposal?

326
00:25:46.840 --> 00:25:49.440
Let's start with your last night
in this world.

327
00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:22.920
Khaleesi.

328
00:26:23.080 --> 00:26:24.760
Come!

329
00:26:26.280 --> 00:26:30.040
He's very strong. Nobody
understands how strong he is.

330
00:26:49.480 --> 00:26:51.240
He will die tonight.
Princess.

331
00:26:51.400 --> 00:26:54.240
He can't. He can't.
I won't let him.

332
00:26:55.160 --> 00:26:57.480
Even a queen
doesn't have that power.

333
00:27:00.560 --> 00:27:02.280
We must go. quickly.

334
00:27:02.400 --> 00:27:04.440
I've heard there's a good port
in Asshai.

335
00:27:04.520 --> 00:27:07.440
- I'm not leaving him.
- He's already gone. khaleesi.

336
00:27:13.280 --> 00:27:16.800
Even if he dies.
why would I run?

337
00:27:18.320 --> 00:27:22.200
I am khaleesi.
My son will be khal after Drogo.

338
00:27:22.960 --> 00:27:25.400
This is not Westeros.
where men honor blood.

339
00:27:26.080 --> 00:27:27.960
Here they only honor strength.

340
00:27:28.080 --> 00:27:30.200
There will be fighting
when Drogo dies.

341
00:27:30.400 --> 00:27:33.120
and whoever wins the fighting
will be the new khal.

342
00:27:33.280 --> 00:27:35.200
He won't want any rivals.

343
00:27:35.320 --> 00:27:38.560
Your boy will be plucked from
your breast and given to the dogs.

344
00:27:40.720 --> 00:27:42.960
I won't leave him.

345
00:27:53.120 --> 00:27:55.080
The wound has festered.

346
00:27:55.400 --> 00:27:57.480
You did this. witch.

347
00:27:58.200 --> 00:28:01.000
Stop it!
I don't want her hurt.

348
00:28:01.280 --> 00:28:04.200
No? You don't want her hurt?

349
00:28:06.480 --> 00:28:08.960
Pray we don't hurt you. too.

350
00:28:09.080 --> 00:28:12.240
You let this witch
lay her hands on our Khal.

351
00:28:14.080 --> 00:28:17.400
Rein in your tongue.
She is still your khaleesi.

352
00:28:17.520 --> 00:28:20.320
Only while
the blood-of-my-blood lives.

353
00:28:23.840 --> 00:28:27.160
When he dies. she is nothing.

354
00:28:32.720 --> 00:28:38.160
I have never been nothing.
I am blood of the dragon.

355
00:28:40.040 --> 00:28:44.720
The dragons are all dead.
khaleesi.

356
00:28:53.200 --> 00:28:55.760
I think you should wear
your armor tonight. ser.

357
00:28:56.200 --> 00:28:58.360
I think you're right.

358
00:29:03.320 --> 00:29:06.400
- You've saved me once more.
- And now you must save him.

359
00:29:07.240 --> 00:29:09.160
He's beyond a healer's skills.

360
00:29:09.520 --> 00:29:11.680
All I can do is ease
his path.

361
00:29:11.800 --> 00:29:14.320
Save him and I will free you.
I swear it.

362
00:29:14.880 --> 00:29:16.960
You must know a way...

363
00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:20.320
some magic...

364
00:29:23.200 --> 00:29:25.200
There is a spell.

365
00:29:25.680 --> 00:29:27.880
Some would say
death is cleaner.

366
00:29:37.960 --> 00:29:40.520
Do it. Save him.

367
00:29:41.720 --> 00:29:43.680
- There is a price.
- You will have gold.

368
00:29:43.760 --> 00:29:46.360
It is not a matter of gold.
This is blood magic.

369
00:29:46.440 --> 00:29:48.720
Only death pays for life.

370
00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:53.960
My death?

371
00:29:54.320 --> 00:29:56.640
No. Not your death. khaleesi.

372
00:29:57.840 --> 00:29:59.960
Bring me his horse.

373
00:30:22.240 --> 00:30:24.120
Khaleesi...
do not do this thing.

374
00:30:24.240 --> 00:30:27.080
- Let me kill this witch.
- Kill her and you kill your khal.

375
00:30:27.480 --> 00:30:29.640
This is bloodmagic.
It is forbidden.

376
00:30:29.840 --> 00:30:32.920
I am your khaleesi.
I tell you what is forbidden.

377
00:30:43.600 --> 00:30:45.320
Go now.

378
00:30:45.440 --> 00:30:47.680
Take her and leave.
Take her!

379
00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:55.760
You must go as well. lady.
Once I begin to sing.

380
00:30:55.840 --> 00:30:59.240
no one may enter the tent.
The dead will dance here tonight.

381
00:31:12.680 --> 00:31:14.560
No one will enter.

382
00:31:22.960 --> 00:31:24.760
Bring him back to me.

383
00:31:40.400 --> 00:31:42.920
- What have you done?
- I have to save him.

384
00:31:44.320 --> 00:31:46.560
We could have been
ten miles from here by now.

385
00:31:46.640 --> 00:31:49.120
on the way to Asshai...
You would have been safe.

386
00:31:57.560 --> 00:31:59.960
- This must not be.
- This must be.

387
00:32:00.800 --> 00:32:02.360
Witch.

388
00:32:03.840 --> 00:32:05.400
No! You can't!

389
00:32:08.680 --> 00:32:10.760
No further. horselord.

390
00:32:50.240 --> 00:32:51.800
Are you hurt?!

391
00:32:51.960 --> 00:32:54.760
- The baby... it's coming...
- Fetch the midwives!

392
00:32:55.200 --> 00:32:57.440
They will not come.
They say she is cursed.

393
00:32:59.400 --> 00:33:01.640
They'll come
or I'll have their heads!

394
00:33:02.480 --> 00:33:05.200
The witch can bring baby.
I hear her say so.

395
00:33:28.680 --> 00:33:30.880
- Are you in agony. my lion?
- No.

396
00:33:31.120 --> 00:33:33.040
You look like you're in agony.

397
00:33:33.560 --> 00:33:35.760
The fire is burning
your pretty soft skin.

398
00:33:42.560 --> 00:33:44.880
Damn you. woman.
Are you immune to pain?

399
00:33:45.120 --> 00:33:47.080
- Just used to it.
- Drink.

400
00:33:49.800 --> 00:33:51.400
Let's play a new game.

401
00:33:52.440 --> 00:33:54.960
There's a Braavosi knife game
I could teach you.

402
00:33:55.320 --> 00:33:57.920
Does it involve the potential
of losing fingers?

403
00:33:58.080 --> 00:33:59.760
Not if you win.

404
00:33:59.920 --> 00:34:05.000
No more fire games. no knife games.
Let's do something I'm good at.

405
00:34:05.800 --> 00:34:07.520
What are you good at?

406
00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:10.040
I happen to be
a great judge of character.

407
00:34:10.120 --> 00:34:11.960
This sounds
like a boring game.

408
00:34:12.040 --> 00:34:15.240
It's not. Here's how it works: I'll
make a statement about your past.

409
00:34:16.360 --> 00:34:18.840
If I'm right. you drink.
If I'm wrong. I drink.

410
00:34:19.040 --> 00:34:21.520
And no lying!
I'll know if you're lying!

411
00:34:22.360 --> 00:34:24.080
I don't want
to play this game.

412
00:34:24.200 --> 00:34:26.120
Fine. Bronn first.

413
00:34:30.240 --> 00:34:31.960
Your father beat you.

414
00:34:37.360 --> 00:34:39.360
But my mother hit harder.

415
00:34:42.640 --> 00:34:45.120
You killed your first man
before you were twelve.

416
00:34:45.240 --> 00:34:46.960
It was a woman.

417
00:34:50.080 --> 00:34:51.960
She was swinging
an axe at me.

418
00:34:52.960 --> 00:34:54.920
You've been north of the Wall.

419
00:34:58.120 --> 00:34:59.920
What brought you up there?

420
00:35:00.920 --> 00:35:02.560
Work.

421
00:35:02.680 --> 00:35:05.440
And... you once loved a woman.
many years ago.

422
00:35:05.600 --> 00:35:09.080
but it turned out badly. so you've
never let yourself love again.

423
00:35:11.160 --> 00:35:12.960
Oh wait. that's me.

424
00:35:16.160 --> 00:35:18.320
Your turn. my mysterious
foreign beauty.

425
00:35:18.440 --> 00:35:20.280
I don't want to play.

426
00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:23.640
It's fun!
Look how much fun we're having!

427
00:35:27.360 --> 00:35:29.240
Your mother was a whore.

428
00:35:30.360 --> 00:35:32.000
Drink.

429
00:35:37.800 --> 00:35:39.440
All right.

430
00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:42.640
Your father left the family
when you were very young.

431
00:35:42.760 --> 00:35:45.000
- Never to return.
- Drink.

432
00:35:45.520 --> 00:35:47.720
And we've established
the rule about lying?

433
00:35:47.800 --> 00:35:49.800
Drink!

434
00:35:55.640 --> 00:35:58.280
You wanted a different life.
You came from somewhere

435
00:35:58.360 --> 00:36:00.240
and you wanted
to be somewhere else.

436
00:36:00.320 --> 00:36:03.320
The whole shit-stained world
could be drinking off that one.

437
00:36:03.400 --> 00:36:05.680
So. specifics.
you wanted to be elsewhere.

438
00:36:05.760 --> 00:36:07.920
but how would you
get there?

439
00:36:08.280 --> 00:36:11.160
I don't think the Silent
Sisters' life is for you.

440
00:36:11.880 --> 00:36:14.600
So what's
a lowborn girl to do?

441
00:36:18.720 --> 00:36:20.560
Drink!

442
00:36:22.600 --> 00:36:24.760
- You're sure...
- Drink!

443
00:36:29.800 --> 00:36:32.680
And don't talk about
my mother and father. Ever.

444
00:36:33.480 --> 00:36:36.120
Or I'll carve your eyes
right out of your head.

445
00:36:40.200 --> 00:36:42.840
If I've offended you.
my lady. I apologize.

446
00:36:44.160 --> 00:36:47.720
- My turn.
- Fine. fine. Ask away.

447
00:36:49.480 --> 00:36:52.120
See if you can penetrate
the enigma that is me!

448
00:36:52.440 --> 00:36:54.040
Who were you in love with?

449
00:36:54.160 --> 00:36:55.800
That's not the way
the game works.

450
00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:57.800
I don't care the way
the game works.

451
00:36:57.880 --> 00:36:59.880
Our lord here
used to be married.

452
00:37:00.600 --> 00:37:02.720
- Married?
- How did you hear that?

453
00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:06.200
You hear lots of things. playing
dice with Lannister soldiers.

454
00:37:08.360 --> 00:37:12.320
- Another night. perhaps.
- Not another night. This night.

455
00:37:14.520 --> 00:37:16.320
It's not a pleasant story.

456
00:37:17.920 --> 00:37:19.600
Maybe I'll cry.

457
00:37:19.680 --> 00:37:22.640
I'm guessing the lady and I can
tell more unpleasant stories

458
00:37:22.720 --> 00:37:24.600
than your lordship.

459
00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:27.680
So...

460
00:37:31.320 --> 00:37:33.720
I was sixteen.
My brother Jaime and I were riding

461
00:37:33.800 --> 00:37:35.640
when we heard a scream.

462
00:37:36.560 --> 00:37:39.520
and she ran into the road.
clothes half torn off.

463
00:37:39.640 --> 00:37:41.520
with two men on her heels.

464
00:37:41.600 --> 00:37:45.000
Jaime scared off the men easy enough
while I wrapped her in my cloak.

465
00:37:45.080 --> 00:37:47.120
She was too scared to send off
on her own.

466
00:37:47.200 --> 00:37:50.080
so while Jaime hunted down
the rapers

467
00:37:50.160 --> 00:37:52.680
I took her
to the nearest inn and fed her.

468
00:37:52.960 --> 00:37:55.800
Her name was Tysha.
She was a wheelwright's orphan.

469
00:37:55.880 --> 00:37:58.080
and she was hungry.

470
00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:01.880
Together we finished three chickens
and a flagon of wine.

471
00:38:02.360 --> 00:38:04.280
Impossible as it seems.
there was a time

472
00:38:04.360 --> 00:38:06.400
when I wasn't accustomed
to wine.

473
00:38:06.680 --> 00:38:10.000
I forgot how afraid I was
around girls. how I kept waiting

474
00:38:10.120 --> 00:38:13.640
for them to laugh at me.
or look away embarrassed.

475
00:38:13.880 --> 00:38:16.400
or ask about my tall
handsome brother.

476
00:38:17.120 --> 00:38:19.360
I forgot about everything
but Tysha.

477
00:38:20.320 --> 00:38:22.720
And somehow.
I found myself in her bed.

478
00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:25.120
For three chickens.
I should hope so.

479
00:38:26.000 --> 00:38:29.000
I didn't last long. I didn't know
what the hell I was doing.

480
00:38:29.400 --> 00:38:32.160
But she was good to me.
she kissed me afterward.

481
00:38:32.640 --> 00:38:37.320
and sang me a song.
and by the morning

482
00:38:37.400 --> 00:38:40.040
I was deep enough in love
to ask for her hand.

483
00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:43.800
A few lies. a few gold coins.
one drunken septon.

484
00:38:43.880 --> 00:38:46.080
and there you have it:
man and wife.

485
00:38:47.240 --> 00:38:49.560
For about a fortnight.
until the septon sobered up

486
00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:51.720
and told my father.

487
00:38:52.680 --> 00:38:54.720
I imagine that was the end
of all that.

488
00:38:54.800 --> 00:38:59.080
Not quite. First. my father
made Jaime tell me the truth.

489
00:39:01.920 --> 00:39:06.320
The girl was a whore. you see.
Jaime had arranged the whole thing.

490
00:39:07.640 --> 00:39:11.880
the road. the rapers. all of it.
He thought it was time I had a woman.

491
00:39:14.840 --> 00:39:19.080
And after Jaime confessed.
my lord father brought my wife in

492
00:39:19.600 --> 00:39:21.640
and gave her to his guards.

493
00:39:23.080 --> 00:39:25.320
He paid her well.
a silver for each man.

494
00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:28.120
How many whores command
that kind of price?

495
00:39:30.520 --> 00:39:32.960
He took me into the barracks
and made me watch.

496
00:39:34.160 --> 00:39:38.080
By the end. she had so many silvers
that the coins were slipping

497
00:39:38.160 --> 00:39:41.120
through her fingers
and rolling onto the floor.

498
00:39:45.520 --> 00:39:47.920
I would have killed the man
who did that to me.

499
00:39:49.160 --> 00:39:51.320
You should have known
she was a whore.

500
00:39:52.160 --> 00:39:55.600
Really? I was sixteen
and drunk and in love.

501
00:39:56.560 --> 00:39:59.200
A girl who is almost raped
does not invite another man

502
00:39:59.280 --> 00:40:01.800
into her bed two hours later.

503
00:40:02.640 --> 00:40:05.400
As I said.
I was young and stupid...

504
00:40:08.640 --> 00:40:11.040
You're still young
and stupid.

505
00:40:51.520 --> 00:40:54.680
- What is it? What do you want?
- You're sleeping through the war.

506
00:40:54.960 --> 00:40:57.840
They stole a night's march on us.
They're a mile north.

507
00:40:59.560 --> 00:41:01.800
- Get my squire.
- You don't have a squire.

508
00:41:04.560 --> 00:41:06.720
If I die. weep for me.

509
00:41:07.640 --> 00:41:10.320
You'll be dead.
How will you know?

510
00:41:16.480 --> 00:41:18.120
I'll know.

511
00:41:20.560 --> 00:41:22.200
Watch out!

512
00:41:32.680 --> 00:41:35.600
- Stay low.
- Stay low?

513
00:41:36.640 --> 00:41:39.000
If you're lucky.
no one will even notice you.

514
00:41:39.280 --> 00:41:41.000
I was born lucky.

515
00:41:43.800 --> 00:41:46.600
Tribesmen of the Vale!
Gather round!

516
00:41:49.480 --> 00:41:54.160
Stone Crows! Burned Men!
Black Ears! Moon Brothers!

517
00:41:54.920 --> 00:41:56.680
Painted Dogs!

518
00:41:56.960 --> 00:42:01.120
And Painted Dogs! Your dominion
over the Vale begins now!

519
00:42:02.000 --> 00:42:04.080
Onward.
to claim what is yours!

520
00:42:04.640 --> 00:42:06.440
Halfman!

521
00:42:07.320 --> 00:42:10.320
Halfman!

522
00:42:12.960 --> 00:42:14.800
To battle!

523
00:42:55.480 --> 00:42:57.640
You're a shit warrior.

524
00:43:00.240 --> 00:43:02.880
- I'm alive?
- You're alive.

525
00:43:09.120 --> 00:43:10.800
Did we win?

526
00:43:10.960 --> 00:43:13.360
Or we wouldn't be having
this conversation.

527
00:43:25.800 --> 00:43:27.840
How did our tribesmen do?

528
00:43:29.400 --> 00:43:31.120
Good.

529
00:43:32.640 --> 00:43:34.800
It's nice to see them
getting along.

530
00:43:35.400 --> 00:43:38.320
- You're wounded.
- Good of you to notice.

531
00:43:40.320 --> 00:43:42.080
I hear we won.

532
00:43:42.840 --> 00:43:46.400
The scouts were wrong. There were
two thousand Stark bannermen.

533
00:43:46.560 --> 00:43:48.400
not twenty.

534
00:43:48.960 --> 00:43:51.120
Did we get the Stark boy.
at least?

535
00:43:51.200 --> 00:43:53.920
- He wasn't here.
- So where was he?

536
00:43:55.120 --> 00:43:57.680
With his other
eighteen thousand men.

537
00:44:00.680 --> 00:44:02.560
And where are they?

538
00:44:12.560 --> 00:44:14.640
- We should go. my lady.
- No.

539
00:44:19.800 --> 00:44:21.920
My lady...

540
00:44:54.840 --> 00:44:56.840
By the time they knew
what was happening.

541
00:44:56.920 --> 00:44:58.680
it had already happened.

542
00:45:02.080 --> 00:45:05.520
Lady Stark. I'd offer you my sword.
but I seem to have lost it.

543
00:45:05.840 --> 00:45:07.720
It's not your sword I want.

544
00:45:09.400 --> 00:45:12.040
Give me my daughters.
Give me my lord husband.

545
00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:15.720
I've lost them. too.
I'm afraid.

546
00:45:15.840 --> 00:45:18.000
Kill him. Robb.
Send his head his father.

547
00:45:18.080 --> 00:45:20.200
He cut down ten of men.
you saw him.

548
00:45:20.520 --> 00:45:22.560
He's more use to us
alive than dead.

549
00:45:22.920 --> 00:45:24.720
Take him away.
put him in irons.

550
00:45:25.960 --> 00:45:29.320
We could end this war right now. boy.
Save thousands of lives.

551
00:45:30.280 --> 00:45:33.000
You fight for the Starks.
I fight for the Lannisters.

552
00:45:33.080 --> 00:45:36.240
Swords or lances or teeth and nails.
chose your weapons

553
00:45:36.440 --> 00:45:38.480
and let's end it
here and now.

554
00:45:41.120 --> 00:45:44.600
If we do it your way.
Kingslayer... you'd win.

555
00:45:48.760 --> 00:45:51.040
We're not doing it
your way...

556
00:45:52.600 --> 00:45:54.560
Come on. pretty man.

557
00:46:02.640 --> 00:46:05.000
I sent two thousand men
to their graves today.

558
00:46:05.120 --> 00:46:07.640
The bards will sing songs
about their sacrifice.

559
00:46:07.720 --> 00:46:10.360
Aye. But the dead
won't hear them.

560
00:46:17.000 --> 00:46:19.200
One victory
does not make us conquerors.

561
00:46:21.360 --> 00:46:25.680
Did we free my father? Did we
rescue my sisters from the Queen?

562
00:46:27.960 --> 00:46:31.040
Did we free the north from those
who want us on our knees?

563
00:46:36.600 --> 00:46:38.360
This war is far from over.

564
00:47:08.960 --> 00:47:11.960
Could I have one?
A lemon one or any of em.

565
00:47:12.360 --> 00:47:14.120
Three coppers.

566
00:47:14.680 --> 00:47:16.360
How about
a nice fat pigeon?

567
00:47:16.480 --> 00:47:18.200
Piss off now. Go on.

568
00:47:19.320 --> 00:47:22.120
Do you have any stale ones
from yesterday? Or a burnt one?

569
00:47:22.240 --> 00:47:24.240
Piss off.

570
00:47:31.000 --> 00:47:32.880
Where you going?
What's happening?

571
00:47:32.960 --> 00:47:34.920
They're taking him
to the sept of Baelor.

572
00:47:35.000 --> 00:47:37.280
- Who?
- The Hand of the King.

573
00:48:43.920 --> 00:48:45.600
Baelor.

574
00:48:45.800 --> 00:48:47.760
Baelor!

575
00:49:14.160 --> 00:49:17.240
I am Eddard Stark.
Lord of Winterfell

576
00:49:18.520 --> 00:49:20.480
and the Hand of the King.

577
00:49:29.280 --> 00:49:31.480
I come before you to confess
my treason

578
00:49:33.000 --> 00:49:34.880
in the sight of gods
and men.

579
00:49:36.720 --> 00:49:38.560
I betrayed the faith
of my king

580
00:49:39.480 --> 00:49:41.480
and the trust
of my friend. Robert.

581
00:49:42.760 --> 00:49:45.080
I swore to defend and protect
his children.

582
00:49:45.960 --> 00:49:49.760
but before his blood was cold
I plotted to murder his son

583
00:49:51.960 --> 00:49:53.960
and seize the throne
for myself.

584
00:50:04.600 --> 00:50:08.280
Let the High Septon and Baelor
the Blessed bear witness

585
00:50:08.480 --> 00:50:10.320
to what I say.

586
00:50:12.520 --> 00:50:17.080
Joffrey Baratheon is the one
true heir to the Iron Throne.

587
00:50:18.560 --> 00:50:22.080
by the grace of all the gods.
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms

588
00:50:23.920 --> 00:50:25.880
and Protector of the Realm.

589
00:50:33.120 --> 00:50:36.200
As we sin. so do we suffer.

590
00:50:37.120 --> 00:50:41.760
This man has confessed his crimes
in the sight of gods and men.

591
00:50:43.880 --> 00:50:50.320
The gods are just but Blessed Baelor
taught us they are also merciful.

592
00:50:54.840 --> 00:50:58.440
What shall be done
with this traitor. Your Grace?

593
00:51:03.520 --> 00:51:06.720
My mother wishes me to let
Lord Eddard join the Night's Watch.

594
00:51:06.840 --> 00:51:09.720
Stripped of all titles and powers.
he would serve the Realm

595
00:51:09.800 --> 00:51:11.680
in permanent exile.

596
00:51:11.760 --> 00:51:15.040
And my Lady Sansa has begged
mercy for her father.

597
00:51:20.120 --> 00:51:22.360
But they have the soft hearts
of women.

598
00:51:23.600 --> 00:51:27.600
So long as I am your king. treason
shall never go unpunished.

599
00:51:29.200 --> 00:51:32.320
Ser Ilyn.
bring me his head!

600
00:51:50.600 --> 00:51:52.560
Put him down!

601
00:51:59.080 --> 00:52:01.120
- Don't look!
- Let me go! Let me go!

602
00:52:01.240 --> 00:52:03.560
Shut your mouth.
Look at me.

603
00:52:05.760 --> 00:52:07.680
Stop!

604
00:52:12.920 --> 00:52:14.880
Stop him!
